the CCM: Concepts underlying the cloud controller manager

(these are dependent on the cloud provider)
- node controller
  * Get
  * List
  * Create
  * Update
  * Watch
  * Delete
- route controller
- service controller
  * List
  * Get
  * Watch
  * Patch
  * Update

- volume controller

https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/architecture/controller/

1. Controller Pattern
- controller tracks at least one k8 resource type
- objects have a spec field that represents the desired state
- each controller(s) has a resource, a resource can have multiplie controllers
- controller sends messages to the API server
